content:
Optimize Dashboard Performance

Before finalizing the dashboard, run a performance check on the dashboard and its queries to ensure everything is running optimally. The dashboard inspector identifies bottlenecks such as slow queries and networks, and provides recommendations to improve performance.

Open the dashboard in view mode and click on the Dashboard Inspector icon. The dashboard inspector collects performance metrics immediately. The Performance tab shows factors by which the dashboard is evaluated.

If a warning icon appears next to a factor, expand it to learn how to fix the issue. Ignore factors with a green checkmark because they don't apply to the dashboard.

To analyze all queries in the dashboard, go to the Query table. The table lists queries that ran when the dashboard loaded and shows metrics for each query, including Max Time (SEC), Maximum execution time on the current dashboard page.

Select a query to view additional details about the query and the last run. For more information about query performance, see Optimize a Query.
title: Optimizing Salesforce Dashboard Performance
